article.headline: Saint Louis 76, Xavier 65
article.story: ST. LOUIS (AP) -- Tommie Liddell had 21 points, five rebounds and four assists to lead Saint Louis University to a 76-65 win over Xavier in Atlantic-10 play Saturday night. Liddell, who has scored 20 or more points the last four games, was a perfect 3-of-3 from behind the arc. The Billikens as a team made 9-of-14 from behind the 3-point line. Kevin Lisch added 19 points for Saint Louis, which moved to 12-5 overall and 2-2 in Atlantic-10 play. Luke Meyer and Dwayne Polk also were in double digits with 12 points each. Drew Lavender had 16 to lead the Musketeers (12-5, 2-1), who had their four-game winning streak snapped. Saint Louis began the game on fire, scoring the games first 10 points and jumping to a 15-2 advantage. Meanwhile, the Musketeers were as cold as the ice falling outside, as Xavier missed its first 12 shots from the field. The Musketeers never did hit a shot from behind the 3-point line in the first 20 minutes. Xavier missed all 14 shots from 3-point range in the first half and finished 8-for-230 from behind the arc. The Billikens also cooled off late in the half, as Saint Louis scored only two points in the final 5:17. But the Billikens still took a 29-17 lead into halftime. Xavier made a slight run at Saint Louis in the second half, and got within as close as six at 71-65 with 1:28 left after Josh Duncan made two free throws. But Lisch and Polk made 5-of-6 free throw attempts down the stretch to seal the win.
